1m LiDAR DEM topo-bathymetric Aude 2020 - ANR PICS
This dataset contains the digital elevation models for the Aude sector as well as the data coverage in the form of a .shp file

The objectives of this LiDAR acquisition are (i) to complete the existing LiDAR coverage of the area, (ii) to generate data of better quality than the DGPR constraints and (iii) to characterise the bathymetry of the rivers at very high resolution (VHR). These data will be used to improve flash flood prediction using the VHR numerical models generated from the LiDAR data and automated flood modelling methods.
